WEBVTT

00:01.610 --> 00:03.177
FAITH:
Previously, onWill Trent...

00:03.220 --> 00:04.178
FRANKLIN: How long
has this been going on for?

00:04.221 --> 00:05.918
25 years.

00:05.962 --> 00:07.659
FRANKLIN: Do you really want
to be in a relationship

00:07.703 --> 00:08.269
with someone who reminds you of
the worst times of your life?

00:08.312 --> 00:09.357
I need a favor.

00:09.400 --> 00:10.749
I want you to talk
about your mom.

00:10.793 --> 00:13.448
I was five the first time
she pimped me out.

00:13.491 --> 00:15.624
-That was a lot to ask.
-It just

00:15.667 --> 00:17.321
made it clear to me
why we don't work.

00:17.365 --> 00:19.584
All we do is remind each other
how broken we are.

00:19.628 --> 00:20.977
ORMEWOOD: I should not
have been in that position.

00:21.021 --> 00:23.110
I just wanted to say
that I'm sorry.

00:23.153 --> 00:24.981
Also, I never told anybody
about us.

00:25.025 --> 00:26.852
Actually, you can tell me
why you're doing this to me.

00:26.896 --> 00:28.115
Putting you
with my best agent?

00:28.158 --> 00:30.247
FAITH: Handcuffing me to this
strange man.

00:30.291 --> 00:31.553
I've known you
your entire life.

00:31.596 --> 00:33.250
Will can take you
to the next level.

00:33.294 --> 00:35.513
You're going to the school
without me, aren't you?

00:35.557 --> 00:36.645
Yes.

00:36.688 --> 00:38.690
[electricity crackles]

00:38.734 --> 00:41.041
This -- This is why
you keep me in the loop.

00:41.084 --> 00:42.477
You did okay.

00:42.520 --> 00:45.045
Thank you for saving
my life today, Faith.

00:48.265 --> 00:51.181
[shaky breathing]

00:52.443 --> 00:56.708
You're okay now.

00:56.752 --> 00:59.363
I got you.

00:59.407 --> 01:01.844
We'll figure this --
[sobbing]

01:01.887 --> 01:02.975
Hey, hey, hey, hey, hey.

01:03.019 --> 01:04.325
-I got you.
-Come on. Come on.

01:04.367 --> 01:05.674
Let's get you back
to your room, Mr. Merrick.

01:05.717 --> 01:06.805
Come on.

01:06.849 --> 01:07.893
That's the third
damn time this week.

01:07.937 --> 01:09.504
You've got
to quit this, okay?

01:09.547 --> 01:11.114
-[sobbing continues]
-Come on. Come on.

01:11.158 --> 01:15.162
-I'm --
-Come on. There you go.

01:15.205 --> 01:16.946
[fire crackling]

01:16.989 --> 01:18.643
Come on.

01:18.687 --> 01:25.650
♪♪

01:25.694 --> 01:28.740
MERRICK: You came back for me!
You came --

01:28.783 --> 01:32.353
-Shh, shh, shh, shh, shh.
-I'm sorry!

01:32.396 --> 01:35.225
I'm sorry.

01:35.269 --> 01:36.966
I'm sorry!

01:38.576 --> 01:40.839
AMANDA: Randy Cordett,
mayor of Oakmeade.

01:40.883 --> 01:42.014
One gunshot
to the shoulder,

01:42.058 --> 01:43.886
second to the head
was fatal.

01:43.929 --> 01:46.062
Then they set
his boat on fire?

01:46.106 --> 01:47.281
That's dramatic.

01:47.324 --> 01:48.543
You think someone's
making a statement?

01:48.586 --> 01:50.675
-Maybe political?
-Or it was ghosts.

01:50.719 --> 01:51.807
It's Lake Lanier.

01:51.850 --> 01:53.548
They stole land,
dug up cemeteries,

01:53.591 --> 01:55.332
or just plowed over them.

01:55.376 --> 01:56.768
And for what?

01:56.812 --> 01:58.901
A tourist spot?

01:58.944 --> 02:00.729
You build a lake over a town
full of Black folks,

02:00.772 --> 02:02.470
you're gonna get a haunted lake.

02:02.513 --> 02:03.906
True, but I need
you both there.

02:03.949 --> 02:06.430
Are we on good terms
with the sheriff in Oakmeade?

02:06.474 --> 02:07.823
She's new,

02:07.866 --> 02:09.607
but I'm hoping less
of a racist pain in the ass

02:09.651 --> 02:11.827
than the last sheriff.

02:11.870 --> 02:13.133
Enjoy the road trip.

02:16.005 --> 02:17.311
Betty likes
a little bit of pumpkin

02:17.353 --> 02:19.051
-with her kibble.
-Got it.

02:19.095 --> 02:20.879
But you gotta make sure
that you mix it well, or else,

02:20.923 --> 02:22.794
you know, she'll just move
the kibble aside

02:22.838 --> 02:24.187
and just only eat
the pumpkin,

02:24.231 --> 02:25.232
'cause she's a smart girl,
aren't you?

02:25.275 --> 02:26.755
-Mm-hmm.
-By the way, whoa.

02:26.798 --> 02:29.366
Make sure that she gets
at least one long walk,

02:29.410 --> 02:30.672
but not too fast.

02:30.715 --> 02:31.934
Did you know that
the leading cause of death

02:31.977 --> 02:33.631
amongst all the Chihuahuas
is heart disease?

02:33.675 --> 02:35.372
Do you want to just
take her with you?

02:36.678 --> 02:38.375
[whispering indistinctly]

02:38.418 --> 02:39.463
[dog whimpers]

02:39.507 --> 02:40.551
[cellphone ringing]

02:40.595 --> 02:42.510
Special Agent Trent.

02:44.642 --> 02:47.210
Um, hi, Ava.

02:49.212 --> 02:51.736
What can I do you for?

02:51.780 --> 02:54.913
♪ Sinner man♪

02:54.957 --> 02:58.439
♪ Oh, sinner man♪

02:59.744 --> 03:01.398
♪ Sinner♪

03:01.442 --> 03:06.316
♪ You can't get away♪

03:08.492 --> 03:10.407
I just re-upped
your laundry card.

03:10.451 --> 03:11.452
Ma, you want your son
out in these streets

03:11.495 --> 03:12.931
looking raggedy?

03:12.975 --> 03:15.195
By "these streets,"
do you mean the campus library?

03:15.238 --> 03:17.632
I don't want to see
another mediocre grade, Jeremy.

03:17.675 --> 03:19.895
Will, how are you doing
on this long drive?

03:19.938 --> 03:21.026
Not good.

03:21.070 --> 03:22.724
Just hoping
I make it there alive.

03:22.767 --> 03:25.292
Where do you even find
a cup holder for dipping sauce?

03:25.335 --> 03:26.554
Ma, you skipped
breakfast again?

03:26.597 --> 03:29.600
-Go, study, now!
-[cellphone beeps]

03:29.644 --> 03:31.167
I can't help but notice
your energy's matching

03:31.211 --> 03:33.517
your car's interior
right now.

03:33.561 --> 03:35.606
It's hectic.
What's up?

03:35.650 --> 03:37.478
It's Lake Lanier.
Creeps me out.

03:37.521 --> 03:39.349
Okay, but ghosts?

03:39.393 --> 03:41.003
How can there not be?

03:41.046 --> 03:43.484
[tire pops, air hisses]

03:43.527 --> 03:44.572
[flat tire clicking]

03:44.615 --> 03:47.270
[brakes screech]

03:47.314 --> 03:48.358
-See?
-[Will sighs]

03:48.402 --> 03:50.186
I knew I should have
driven myself.

03:50.230 --> 03:51.492
You probably hit a rock.

03:51.535 --> 03:53.015
Can you just be helpful
and call for a tow?

03:53.058 --> 03:54.321
My phone's in the back.

03:54.364 --> 03:55.365
Your phone's
in front of you.

03:55.409 --> 03:56.888
No, this is my
Jeremy-phone.

03:56.932 --> 03:57.976
-Why do you have two --
-Can you just --

03:58.020 --> 03:59.108
Fine!

03:59.151 --> 04:00.152
Pop the trunk.

04:00.196 --> 04:01.458
I'll put on the spare.

04:01.502 --> 04:04.418
Actually, I want you
to time me.

04:04.461 --> 04:07.072
FAITH: Yeah, no. Will.

04:07.116 --> 04:09.336
Will, we're driving
on the spare.

04:10.728 --> 04:11.860
How?

04:11.903 --> 04:13.253
How do you live
like this?

04:16.298 --> 04:18.475
You don't have a single tire
in all this mess?

04:18.519 --> 04:21.086
It's not mess.
This is beautiful.

04:21.130 --> 04:22.523
OTIS: Look, ma'am,
I'm real sorry,

04:22.566 --> 04:24.873
but folks around here
don't drive these tiny cars.

04:24.916 --> 04:26.483
Now, I can get you one
in a few days.

04:26.527 --> 04:29.399
Is that a whole box
of Silverados?

04:29.443 --> 04:31.314
-Silverado Pitmans are --
-FAITH: I don't care.

04:31.358 --> 04:34.056
Got over five grand
in that box alone.

04:34.099 --> 04:36.667
Just out in the open, huh?

04:36.711 --> 04:37.973
Trust me, brother.

04:38.016 --> 04:40.845
They're safe.

04:40.889 --> 04:42.717
WILL: This out here,
this is you, too?

04:42.760 --> 04:45.241
This is a gold mine.

04:45.284 --> 04:46.851
I restored my '73 Targa.

04:46.895 --> 04:49.463
It would have been much faster
if I had half of this stuff.

04:49.506 --> 04:52.248
Hey, I heard what happened
to the mayor.

04:52.292 --> 04:53.423
That's wild, huh?

04:53.467 --> 04:55.599
Yeah, me and Randy,
we grew up together,

04:55.643 --> 04:57.340
all the way up through
high school.

04:57.384 --> 04:59.864
'Course, he got elected
and did what they all do --

04:59.908 --> 05:01.692
screw the working man,
right?

05:01.736 --> 05:03.041
FAITH: He won his reelection
by a considerable margin,

05:03.085 --> 05:04.782
though, didn't he?

05:04.826 --> 05:07.350
Well, yeah, but that's just
'cause people are sheep.

05:07.394 --> 05:08.960
Not me.

05:09.004 --> 05:10.353
I'm prepared
for what's coming.

05:10.397 --> 05:11.789
What do you think
the mayor was involved in?

05:11.833 --> 05:13.356
Think?

05:13.400 --> 05:14.575
Brother, I know.

05:16.620 --> 05:18.579
He was one
of the lizard people.

05:18.622 --> 05:25.020
♪♪

05:25.063 --> 05:26.413
ANGIE: All right.

05:26.456 --> 05:28.980
So what is it?
Accident or homicide?

05:29.024 --> 05:30.547
ORMEWOOD:
He just fell, right?

05:30.591 --> 05:33.376
Well, your guy definitely
would have died from the fall,

05:33.420 --> 05:37.467
but see the gravel
settled around the edges?

05:37.511 --> 05:38.512
♪♪

05:38.555 --> 05:40.557
Yeah, sure.
So what?

05:40.601 --> 05:43.038
The gravel
isn't embedded.

05:43.081 --> 05:46.433
That means someone hit your guy
on the noggin so hard

05:46.476 --> 05:50.524
it sent him sailing,
and then, thud.

05:50.567 --> 05:53.135
ANGIE: Hey, thanks
for coming in, Mr. Parnell.

05:53.178 --> 05:55.790
So why don't you, uh,
tell us what you saw?

05:55.832 --> 05:57.966
So I'm doing my outside check
of a new apartment building --

05:58.009 --> 05:59.837
it's gonna be nice,
by the way --

05:59.881 --> 06:01.404
but I told them
I'm not going up inside,

06:01.448 --> 06:03.145
not 'til the building's
done passing code

06:03.188 --> 06:04.494
and the windows are in.

06:04.538 --> 06:06.322
And look what happened.
You see what happened?

06:06.366 --> 06:08.629
No, why don't you finish
telling us what happened?

06:08.672 --> 06:10.195
Well, John --
that's the other guard,

06:10.239 --> 06:11.371
-the one that died --
-Uh-huh.

06:11.414 --> 06:13.938
I hear John yell
for someone, "Stop!"

06:13.982 --> 06:15.897
So I look through a hole
where a window's gonna be,

06:15.940 --> 06:17.638
I see this idiot spin around,

06:17.681 --> 06:19.683
a bunch of copper plumbing
slung over his shoulder.

06:19.727 --> 06:21.685
Idiot?
Why an idiot?

06:21.729 --> 06:23.034
'Cause he was an idiot.

06:23.078 --> 06:24.471
One of the pipes knocks John
right in the head,

06:24.514 --> 06:25.994
sends him flying out
the window --

06:26.037 --> 06:27.082
or where the window's gonna be,

06:27.125 --> 06:28.518
-you know.
-Right.

06:28.562 --> 06:30.259
Then the guy runs out
the building straight at me.

06:30.302 --> 06:33.175
[scoffs] I didn't move,
and he says "'Scuse me."

06:33.218 --> 06:36.657
Now I done seen the idiot's face
and heard the idiot's voice.

06:36.700 --> 06:38.093
Great.

06:38.136 --> 06:39.355
Thank you so much.

06:39.399 --> 06:40.922
We'll have you look
at some photos now, okay?

06:41.792 --> 06:43.446
Thought you'd be happier
about an easier solve.

06:43.490 --> 06:44.752
"I'm coming for
Will Trent's record."

06:44.795 --> 06:45.840
I don't sound
like that.

06:45.883 --> 06:47.494
Look, I need to --

06:47.537 --> 06:49.626
Do you want to come over
to dinner tomorrow night?

06:49.670 --> 06:51.367
No.
Why would I --

06:51.411 --> 06:52.455
Is your wife
gonna be there?

06:52.499 --> 06:54.283
Of course she is.
It was her idea.

06:54.326 --> 06:55.980
Somebody invite me to dinner,
I'm going.

06:56.024 --> 06:58.287
-You should go.
-Shh.

06:58.330 --> 07:00.811
C-Can --
Does she know that we --

07:00.855 --> 07:01.856
No, dummy.

07:01.899 --> 07:02.900
Why would she invite you
to our home

07:02.944 --> 07:04.380
-if she knew we had sex?
-I --

07:04.424 --> 07:06.295
No, she just wants
to get to know my new partner.

07:06.338 --> 07:07.949
-That's all.
-No.

07:11.169 --> 07:14.782
Oh, I'm very glad GBI is here.

07:14.825 --> 07:17.175
You know, we don't see this
kind of thing very often.

07:17.219 --> 07:18.960
Occasional B and E,
kids out drinking.

07:19.003 --> 07:20.178
That's about it.

07:20.222 --> 07:21.441
However we can help,
Sheriff.

07:21.484 --> 07:22.877
And thank you for having
the boat brought here.

07:22.920 --> 07:25.009
Oh, of course.
And please, call me Josie.

07:25.053 --> 07:26.489
The ME said
the shot to the shoulder

07:26.533 --> 07:27.838
was from
a long-range gun?

07:27.882 --> 07:29.492
That's right.

07:29.536 --> 07:30.885
Excuse me.

07:31.799 --> 07:35.803
FAITH: So, this is the mayor's
private dock.

07:35.846 --> 07:38.240
Surprisingly nice.

07:38.283 --> 07:40.895
Lake Lanier's tranquility is...
a contradiction.

07:40.938 --> 07:42.026
[scoffs]

07:43.201 --> 07:45.377
Mayor was on his boat.

07:45.421 --> 07:48.729
The shooter was out here
somewhere on land.

07:48.772 --> 07:51.383
Why so far?

07:51.427 --> 07:53.473
They're experienced.

07:53.516 --> 07:55.431
Over-confident that
they'd hit their target.

07:56.258 --> 07:58.173
But the first shot
didn't kill him.

07:58.216 --> 07:59.653
♪♪

07:59.696 --> 08:02.177
There's blood here.

08:02.220 --> 08:03.395
Faith!

08:03.439 --> 08:08.270
♪♪

08:08.313 --> 08:10.011
Sheriff, would you bag this?

08:10.054 --> 08:11.491
Think that's
the killer's blood?

08:11.534 --> 08:13.580
Running with adrenaline.

08:13.623 --> 08:16.408
They didn't even notice
they were cut.

08:16.452 --> 08:18.019
You know what, Faith?

08:18.062 --> 08:20.195
Come at me like you
want to kill me.

08:20.238 --> 08:21.370
Gladly.
[chuckles]

08:21.413 --> 08:22.719
WILL: Okay.

08:22.763 --> 08:24.852
So the killer boarded the boat.

08:24.895 --> 08:26.288
The mayor was fighting
for his life.

08:26.331 --> 08:28.508
They fight, they fight,
they fight,

08:28.551 --> 08:30.466
then the killer
shoots the mayor, bam.

08:30.510 --> 08:32.990
Leaves the dead body
hanging off the boat.

08:33.034 --> 08:34.121
Like a warning.

08:34.164 --> 08:36.341
Well, that's quite a jump.

08:36.385 --> 08:38.386
It's a thought.
You aske--

08:38.429 --> 08:39.562
Didn't he just ask
for my help?

08:39.606 --> 08:41.085
WILL: It was the blood.

08:41.129 --> 08:44.174
The killer realized their blood
was all over the boat,

08:44.219 --> 08:46.569
and so they...

08:46.613 --> 08:48.005
Come on. So they...

08:48.049 --> 08:49.180
Burned the evidence.

08:49.224 --> 08:50.965
Very good.

08:51.008 --> 08:52.270
FAITH: What are you doing
right now?

08:52.314 --> 08:53.620
Amanda asked me to mentor you.

08:53.663 --> 08:55.273
There's still DNA on that nail.

08:55.317 --> 08:56.753
That's who killed the mayor.

08:56.797 --> 08:59.277
♪♪

08:59.321 --> 09:01.410
Whew, talk about
over-confident.

09:01.453 --> 09:03.412
Oh, you have no idea.

09:03.455 --> 09:05.936
WILL: Do you know if
your husband had any enemies,

09:05.980 --> 09:07.285
political or otherwise?

09:07.329 --> 09:09.461
Uh, someone's always

09:09.505 --> 09:10.985
pitching a fit
over a land easement

09:11.028 --> 09:13.074
or the high school
teaching Anne Frank,

09:13.117 --> 09:15.729
but nothing worth
killing a man over.

09:15.772 --> 09:16.773
FAITH:
Any recent visitors?

09:16.817 --> 09:19.602
Arguments you may
have overheard?

09:19.646 --> 09:21.909
I-I'm sorry.
No.

09:21.952 --> 09:24.520
If you think of anything,
anything at all,

09:24.564 --> 09:26.043
give us a call.

09:29.090 --> 09:31.005
Um, it --
it's probably nothing,

09:31.048 --> 09:32.659
but maybe a week ago,

09:32.702 --> 09:36.706
somebody left a --
a toy on our doorstep.

09:36.750 --> 09:38.142
It was one
of those little cars

09:38.186 --> 09:40.405
that kids race
with the tracks.

09:40.449 --> 09:44.148
This was, um,
a station wagon, orange.

09:44.192 --> 09:46.324
With wood paneling?
Oh, my gosh.

09:46.368 --> 09:47.717
Hold it down, Deputy.

09:47.761 --> 09:48.979
Sorry.

09:49.023 --> 09:52.940
So you found a toy car
on the porch.

09:52.983 --> 09:54.724
Did that seem strange to you?

09:54.768 --> 09:56.073
The toy, no.

09:56.117 --> 09:57.858
Just kids, probably.

09:57.901 --> 10:03.428
But Randy, he got so upset,
and that was odd.

10:03.472 --> 10:05.126
He needs to watch
his blood pressure.

10:05.169 --> 10:06.780
I-I keep telling him.
[sobs]

10:06.823 --> 10:08.782
JOSIE: Thanks, Irene.

10:08.825 --> 10:10.261
I'll be in touch.

10:10.305 --> 10:14.265
♪♪

10:14.309 --> 10:16.616
Deputy Riley,
bring it in!

10:16.659 --> 10:18.400
♪♪

10:18.443 --> 10:21.490
We, uh, pulled this off
Allen Cramer, a local.

10:21.533 --> 10:24.101
His body was found in the woods
a few days ago.

10:24.145 --> 10:25.363
Why didn't you mention
that sooner?

10:25.407 --> 10:26.756
Well, everything pointed
to Cramer's death

10:26.800 --> 10:28.062
being a hunting accident.

10:28.105 --> 10:29.324
Start of the season,

10:29.367 --> 10:31.761
a lot of eager folks
with no experience.

10:31.805 --> 10:33.894
A safety vest --
he -- he wasn't wearing one.

10:33.937 --> 10:35.591
Yes, Deputy Riley,

10:35.635 --> 10:37.549
it's unfortunate,
but not unusual.

10:37.593 --> 10:40.552
So now we have two bodies,

10:40.596 --> 10:42.685
both with the same token
left behind?

10:42.729 --> 10:44.731
♪♪

10:44.774 --> 10:46.689
Great.

10:47.603 --> 10:49.605
I knew that car
sounded familiar.

10:49.649 --> 10:51.651
I made some calls to confirm.

10:51.694 --> 10:53.696
There was a case there
30 years ago --

10:53.740 --> 10:55.306
involved an orange
station wagon.

10:55.350 --> 10:56.656
Was it a homicide?

10:56.699 --> 10:58.048
Three.

10:58.092 --> 11:00.529
A couple and their teenage son.

11:00.572 --> 11:04.228
Minding their Black business
one Saturday afternoon --

11:04.272 --> 11:05.969
Fourth of July weekend.

11:06.013 --> 11:07.884
And the whole family
was killed?

11:07.928 --> 11:10.974
In their station wagon.
[sighs]

11:11.018 --> 11:12.672
The case was never solved.

11:12.715 --> 11:14.543
Should have been open and shut,

11:14.586 --> 11:16.806
but the sheriff back then,
he just looked the other way.

11:16.850 --> 11:19.461
Sheriff Miller, you didn't hear
about that case?

11:19.504 --> 11:21.202
I was a baby
when that happened,

11:21.245 --> 11:23.552
and I'm from Arkansas,
so no.

11:23.595 --> 11:25.641
The mayor, the hunter,
and the family

11:25.685 --> 11:28.165
killed in that station wagon
30 years ago.

11:28.209 --> 11:31.255
They're all connected.
Let's find out how.

11:32.387 --> 11:39.437
♪♪

11:39.699 --> 11:40.961
[door thuds]

11:41.004 --> 11:43.398
-Can you move your --
-Would you just hold on?

11:43.441 --> 11:45.487
One room.
One damn room.

11:45.530 --> 11:47.445
Stupid Buck-o-Rama
convention.

11:47.489 --> 11:49.491
Oh, is it hard sharing a room
with another person?

11:49.534 --> 11:51.711
Try six, and the kid
in the top bunk's a bed-wetter.

11:51.754 --> 11:53.234
Oh, how'd you get
the top bunk?

11:53.277 --> 11:56.106
Good one.
'Bout damn time.

11:57.238 --> 11:59.849
[obnoxious laughter]

12:03.331 --> 12:05.420
WILL: What's scarier, a bunch
of white folks with guns,

12:05.463 --> 12:07.814
or ghosts?

12:07.857 --> 12:10.294
It's not funny.

12:10.338 --> 12:11.905
Bad things happened
when they built this town

12:11.948 --> 12:13.994
and that lake,
and it creeps me out.

12:14.037 --> 12:16.213
Some stuff you gotta
compartmentalize.

12:16.257 --> 12:17.519
Get the job done.

12:17.562 --> 12:20.043
Oh, is that what you do --
compartmentalize?

12:20.087 --> 12:21.610
Like when you
beat up Paul Campano

12:21.653 --> 12:23.307
in the middle
of the GBI?

12:23.351 --> 12:25.222
I didn't say it was
a perfect system.

12:26.571 --> 12:28.182
Growing up
in the children's home,

12:28.225 --> 12:31.663
you learn to bury your feelings
in boxes quickly.

12:31.707 --> 12:34.536
Sometimes it comes up
in an active kidnapping case.

12:34.579 --> 12:37.278
Other times,
when you're grocery shopping.

12:37.321 --> 12:40.847
That is the most personal thing
you've ever told me.

12:40.890 --> 12:42.196
-Hmm.
-FAITH: You know what?

12:42.239 --> 12:43.545
Actually, keep going.

12:43.588 --> 12:47.418
Tell me something else.
One thing, partner.

12:48.593 --> 12:49.899
You were right.

12:49.943 --> 12:51.248
I have a date.

12:51.292 --> 12:52.423
And what about Angie?

12:52.467 --> 12:53.990
I didn't say I was going.

12:54.034 --> 12:55.296
You didn't answer
my question.

12:55.339 --> 12:57.254
It's complicated.

12:57.298 --> 12:58.778
I've known Ange forever,

12:58.821 --> 13:03.173
but there are parts of her
she holds back from me,

13:03.217 --> 13:04.871
like a wall
I'm never gonna get past.

13:04.914 --> 13:07.047
Sounds familiar.

13:07.090 --> 13:08.657
You know what?
I think you should go.

13:08.700 --> 13:09.745
Have fun.

13:09.789 --> 13:11.834
She mentioned
a gallery opening.

13:11.878 --> 13:13.270
Definitely don't
wear that suit.

13:13.314 --> 13:15.795
♪♪

13:15.838 --> 13:17.100
WILL: Something's off.

13:17.144 --> 13:19.276
Everyone's claiming
their spot

13:19.320 --> 13:20.582
for Fourth of July
fireworks,

13:20.625 --> 13:23.106
but the family parked
all the way over here

13:23.150 --> 13:24.281
under these trees.

13:24.325 --> 13:26.631
The report says
that there was a witness.

13:27.981 --> 13:31.288
Got it. Witness saw four men
at the scene, Ford Bronco.

13:31.332 --> 13:33.334
They gave the sheriff
a partial plate,

13:33.377 --> 13:36.380
but [chuckles] of course,
the sheriff never followed up.

13:36.424 --> 13:37.555
Sheriff Merrick...

13:38.818 --> 13:41.255
...why the hell'd
you bury this case?

13:41.298 --> 13:43.431
♪♪

13:43.474 --> 13:45.085
Anything, man?
We've been here all day.

13:45.128 --> 13:47.087
Thinner -- I told you
he was much thinner.

13:47.130 --> 13:49.002
Okay.

13:50.438 --> 13:52.135
It's a meal, Ange, okay?

13:52.179 --> 13:53.354
It'll be a little awkward.

13:53.397 --> 13:54.834
It's just --
It's like traffic.

13:54.877 --> 13:56.444
You sit through it
and it's over with, okay?

13:56.487 --> 13:57.924
It's not like
we're screwing anymore.

13:57.967 --> 14:00.448
We were not screw-ing.
It was one time.

14:00.491 --> 14:02.406
Whoa, whoa, whoa.
Hold on, hold on.

14:02.450 --> 14:04.017
Y'all didn't mention
y'all were intimate.

14:04.060 --> 14:06.715
That changes everything.
Don't go over there.

14:06.758 --> 14:08.673
-Just find the perp.
-Shut up.

14:08.717 --> 14:09.979
Found him right here.

14:10.023 --> 14:11.938
-Really?
-Mm-hmm.

14:11.981 --> 14:13.113
You sure?

14:13.156 --> 14:15.767
Yeah, that's him.

14:15.811 --> 14:17.900
Unless he has a twin.

14:17.944 --> 14:23.471
♪♪

14:23.514 --> 14:25.342
Oh, you gotta
be kidding me.

14:25.386 --> 14:26.866
Wait, what?

14:26.909 --> 14:29.912
Our guy is an identical
triplet.

14:29.956 --> 14:32.132
No.

14:33.350 --> 14:34.569
Ooh!
Oh, God.

14:35.526 --> 14:36.963
Really?
Why?

14:37.006 --> 14:38.965
Well, good morning
to you, too.

14:39.008 --> 14:41.706
Look, I couldn't
sit still last night.

14:41.750 --> 14:44.884
This station wagon case
bugged me even as a rookie cop,

14:44.927 --> 14:46.537
but I had no power back then.

14:46.581 --> 14:48.322
Well, that's not
an issue now.

14:48.365 --> 14:49.889
You damn right.

14:49.932 --> 14:52.500
I'm taking up space and flexing
some serious GBI muscle.

14:52.543 --> 14:54.415
We are solving this thing.

14:54.458 --> 14:56.678
-You up for this, Sheriff?
-Yes, ma'am.

14:56.721 --> 14:58.332
AMANDA: All right.

14:58.375 --> 15:00.551
I ran the partial plates the
witness got off the Bronco --

15:00.595 --> 15:02.466
-40,000 hits.
-Oh, needle in a haystack.

15:02.510 --> 15:04.033
No, I'm not done yet.

15:04.077 --> 15:05.426
I cross-checked the vehicles

15:05.469 --> 15:07.167
registered at the time
of the killings

15:07.210 --> 15:10.300
to our most recent victims.

15:10.344 --> 15:11.432
Found our needle.

15:11.475 --> 15:13.347
♪♪

15:13.390 --> 15:15.915
Allen Cramer,
the dead hunter.

15:15.958 --> 15:18.700
Okay, so we have four men
in this Bronco --

15:18.743 --> 15:20.571
one's Allen Cramer.

15:20.615 --> 15:22.443
Mayor Cordett
was raised here.

15:22.486 --> 15:24.010
He might have been
one of them.

15:24.053 --> 15:25.489
Yeah, somebody thought so.
They're both dead days apart.

15:25.533 --> 15:27.230
What if one
of the remaining two

15:27.274 --> 15:28.971
were trying to keep
Cordett and Cramer quiet?

15:29.015 --> 15:30.799
Yeah, but why now?

15:30.842 --> 15:32.366
We need to find
those last two...

15:32.409 --> 15:33.540
alive.

15:33.584 --> 15:35.412
They need to pay
for what they did.

15:35.456 --> 15:37.675
Well, the original eyewitness
who saw the Bronco

15:37.719 --> 15:39.329
died over 10 years ago.

15:39.373 --> 15:42.942
Internet wasn't around,
no social media to rely on.

15:42.985 --> 15:45.205
[chuckles] Children.

15:45.248 --> 15:48.382
Before there was social media,
th-- there were these things

15:48.425 --> 15:49.731
with pages.

15:49.774 --> 15:51.733
Ah. Newspapers.

15:51.776 --> 15:54.344
I have a contact
who can help. [laughs]

15:54.388 --> 15:55.998
I'll drive.

15:56.042 --> 15:58.044
Actually, the former sheriff --
can you get me his address?

15:58.087 --> 16:01.177
I'd like to ask him why he
didn't follow up on that Bronco.

16:01.221 --> 16:02.874
Good luck with that.

16:04.137 --> 16:08.532
I'm here to ask you about an
investigation that you handled.

16:08.576 --> 16:10.099
It was quite awhile ago,

16:10.143 --> 16:12.319
so whatever details
you can provide --

16:12.362 --> 16:13.973
They've come for me?

16:15.322 --> 16:17.150
Your family?

16:17.193 --> 16:20.283
Let's start
with what happened.

16:21.632 --> 16:23.591
Walk me through it.
You got a call.

16:23.634 --> 16:26.463
MERRICK: A call -- lo--
lots of calls.

16:26.507 --> 16:27.725
Complaints.

16:27.769 --> 16:29.336
Tell me about the call

16:29.379 --> 16:32.165
about the station wagon,
the family.

16:32.208 --> 16:33.949
[crickets chirping,
leaves rustling]

16:33.993 --> 16:40.347
MERRICK: It was the most
terrible thing I'd ever seen.

16:40.390 --> 16:42.175
Tell me
what you found.

16:42.218 --> 16:46.570
[sobbing] The --
The worst part was --

16:46.614 --> 16:48.790
was the noise.

16:48.833 --> 16:50.313
What noise?

16:51.445 --> 16:54.187
You're okay.

16:54.230 --> 16:56.450
I've got you.

16:56.493 --> 16:59.105
I got you.

16:59.148 --> 17:00.802
Who do you have?

17:00.845 --> 17:02.717
Who are you talking to?

17:02.760 --> 17:05.111
Was the father still alive
when you arrived?

17:05.154 --> 17:07.896
I got you. [sobbing]

17:07.939 --> 17:09.289
-I'll fix this.
-Shh, shh, shh, shh, shh, shh.

17:09.332 --> 17:10.464
Quiet down. Breathe.

17:10.507 --> 17:12.335
Shh, shh, shh,
shh, shh, shh.

17:12.378 --> 17:14.468
What happened
to the station wagon?

17:14.511 --> 17:16.078
Where's the car?

17:16.122 --> 17:17.384
Excuse me.
What's happening?

17:17.426 --> 17:19.167
Okay, I need you both
to step outside.

17:19.212 --> 17:22.171
[sobbing continues]

17:22.214 --> 17:23.999
♪♪

17:24.042 --> 17:25.305
WILL: How long
has he been like this?

17:25.348 --> 17:27.220
Well, he started
slipping away two years ago,

17:27.262 --> 17:29.439
but lately --

17:29.483 --> 17:31.659
His nurse called,
told me I should come.

17:31.702 --> 17:33.922
Got back in town yesterday.

17:33.965 --> 17:36.838
So what's this really about?

17:36.881 --> 17:39.623
GBI's investigating one
of your father's old cases --

17:39.667 --> 17:41.451
a multiple homicide
of a Black family

17:41.495 --> 17:43.671
killed in their
station wagon.

17:43.714 --> 17:46.239
Yeah, that.

17:46.282 --> 17:49.677
Pops got messed up over
what happened with that family.

17:49.720 --> 17:51.548
Yeah, I guess it makes sense
that he's still --

17:51.592 --> 17:53.115
Haunted?

17:53.159 --> 17:54.812
He ever talk to you about it?

17:54.856 --> 17:56.423
No, no, I heard second hand
from my mom.

17:56.466 --> 17:58.294
I was already away at college.

17:58.338 --> 18:00.253
I'd like to speak
with your mother.

18:01.254 --> 18:02.646
She passed away
six years ago.

18:04.170 --> 18:05.519
Agent Trent, I hope you find
what you need,

18:05.562 --> 18:09.088
but please, let him be.

18:09.131 --> 18:14.136
♪♪

18:15.355 --> 18:16.704
We know you did it.

18:18.053 --> 18:19.054
I'm trying
to help you.

18:19.098 --> 18:20.186
Do you really
want to do time

18:20.229 --> 18:21.578
for what
your brother did?

18:21.622 --> 18:22.884
[yawns]

18:22.927 --> 18:24.842
Your brothers
already sold you out!

18:24.886 --> 18:27.193
[laughs] No, they didn't.

18:27.236 --> 18:29.412
Stonewall me --

18:31.197 --> 18:32.937
[officers laughing]

18:32.981 --> 18:34.287
Oh, you think this is funny?

18:34.330 --> 18:36.115
Yeah,
it's pretty funny.

18:36.811 --> 18:37.812
Shut up, Franklin.

18:37.855 --> 18:39.596
-You asked.
-Hey, it's my case, too.

18:39.640 --> 18:41.468
Hey, I got a plan.
Back me up.

18:41.511 --> 18:42.817
Uh, wait, wait, wait.

18:42.860 --> 18:44.166
Don't mess around
and get our case thrown out.

18:44.210 --> 18:45.646
What the hell do you think
I'm gonna do?

18:45.689 --> 18:48.083
I don't know, excessive force
comes to mind.

18:48.127 --> 18:50.303
This works on my kids
every time, okay?

18:50.346 --> 18:52.479
Nobody wants to go down
for something their sibling did.

18:52.522 --> 18:54.916
Eventually, two of them are
gonna turn on the guilty one.

18:54.959 --> 18:57.179
All right,
let's do it.

19:01.705 --> 19:03.925
-AMANDA: Hey, T. [chuckles]
-THERESA: Hey, how you doing?

19:03.968 --> 19:05.144
Hi.

19:05.187 --> 19:07.320
Theresa's a pioneer
in Black journalism.

19:07.363 --> 19:08.843
She ran the Crusader
for 40 years.

19:08.886 --> 19:10.453
42.

19:10.497 --> 19:11.846
But what is time.

19:11.889 --> 19:13.804
Come on.
The files are out back.

19:13.848 --> 19:15.023
I like you in that green.

19:15.066 --> 19:16.242
You're looking good as ever.

19:16.285 --> 19:18.200
Mandy, why don't you
come into the house

19:18.244 --> 19:21.029
and I'll get you
a cup of iced tea?

19:21.072 --> 19:22.465
You still
like it sweet?

19:22.509 --> 19:24.119
Stop playing, T.
You know how I like it.

19:24.163 --> 19:25.164
[laughs]

19:25.207 --> 19:26.687
I'm sorry,
can we, um --

19:26.730 --> 19:29.211
Ms. Rothwell, your paper covered
the station wagon murders?

19:29.255 --> 19:31.692
Well, big city papers
certainly didn't.

19:31.735 --> 19:35.086
I mean, nobody here
actually believed

19:35.130 --> 19:38.046
that justice would be served,
but a whole family?

19:38.089 --> 19:40.091
[scoffs]
Lord help.

19:40.135 --> 19:42.006
Everything you need
are in the boxes out back.

19:42.050 --> 19:43.356
You just need to sift
through them.

19:43.399 --> 19:45.575
Back in the day,
I took pictures of everything.

19:45.619 --> 19:47.229
-Thank you.
-Mm-hmm.

19:47.273 --> 19:48.404
[Amanda chuckles]

19:48.448 --> 19:49.449
[whispering]
Well, how you been?

19:49.492 --> 19:51.364
-I've been fine.
-[chuckles]

19:51.407 --> 19:53.540
JOSIE: Yes, she did.
Called the cops on me.

19:53.583 --> 19:56.151
Said I was stealing
a patrol car.

19:56.195 --> 19:57.500
While you were
in uniform?

19:57.544 --> 19:59.894
Girl, yes.
It was my first week.

19:59.937 --> 20:03.202
That shirt was crisp.
The badge, shimmering.

20:03.245 --> 20:04.507
I should have arrested her
on principle.

20:04.551 --> 20:06.248
-Absolutely.
-[laughs]

20:06.292 --> 20:08.294
You know, when I first started,
I had this former captain say

20:08.337 --> 20:09.512
that he couldn't promote me

20:09.556 --> 20:12.428
because it was against
the Constitution.

20:12.472 --> 20:13.734
-Former captain?
-FAITH: Mm-hmm.

20:13.777 --> 20:15.344
He get transferred,
or you?

20:15.388 --> 20:17.172
Oh, I had friends in higher
places than he realized.

20:17.216 --> 20:18.826
He got decertified.

20:18.869 --> 20:20.828
Amanda did that for you?

20:20.871 --> 20:22.177
No.

20:22.221 --> 20:23.613
It was actually my mother,

20:23.657 --> 20:25.006
but she's no longer
on the force.

20:25.049 --> 20:27.051
Oh.
By choice?

20:27.095 --> 20:30.707
Um, let's just
say that...

20:30.751 --> 20:35.364
she crossed a line
and lost purpose.

20:36.713 --> 20:38.367
It happens.

20:38.411 --> 20:40.064
I'm sorry.

20:43.416 --> 20:45.592
Where did Amanda
and Theresa disappear to?

20:45.635 --> 20:46.854
Oh, no.
Unh-unh.

20:46.897 --> 20:48.595
I do not want that information
in my head.

20:48.638 --> 20:52.120
-I am good. Thank you so much.
-[both chuckle]

20:52.163 --> 20:53.295
Oh, hold up.

20:53.339 --> 20:55.297
July 4, 1994.

20:55.341 --> 20:57.734
That's it. That's the day
of the murders.

20:59.170 --> 21:01.085
Oh, wait.
Let me see this one.

21:01.129 --> 21:02.130
FAITH: Is that the Bronco?

21:02.173 --> 21:03.436
JOSIE: Do the plates match?

21:03.479 --> 21:07.918
♪♪

21:07.962 --> 21:10.181
FAITH: Mm-hmm.
There they are.

21:10.225 --> 21:11.705
I can't see this one's face.
I need to see his face.

21:11.748 --> 21:14.142
We'll figure it out. Do you
recognize any of the others?

21:14.185 --> 21:16.318
JOSIE: Uh, man on the right,
that's Cramer.

21:16.362 --> 21:17.798
The hunter.
Are you sure?

21:17.841 --> 21:19.408
Yep, and the green shirt,
that's Mayor Cordett.

21:19.452 --> 21:20.583
More hair,
but that's him.

21:20.627 --> 21:22.542
FAITH: The other one
looks so familiar,

21:22.585 --> 21:23.760
but I just can't place him.

21:23.804 --> 21:25.849
[sighs] I'm trying
to imagine him older,

21:25.893 --> 21:27.677
more facial hair,
maybe?

21:27.721 --> 21:28.809
Well, don't have
to imagine.

21:28.852 --> 21:30.593
GBI flex.
Let's go.

21:35.163 --> 21:42.213
♪♪

21:43.389 --> 21:45.216
This must be you, huh?

21:45.260 --> 21:47.654
Yeah, I saw you walk in
for your coffee.

21:47.697 --> 21:49.220
-Did you --
-LOCAL MAN: Yeah.

21:49.264 --> 21:51.745
'Cause I figured if you could
take up two parking spots,

21:51.788 --> 21:54.617
I can spread myself out
as much as I want.

21:57.141 --> 21:58.839
AMANDA: Let's go.

21:58.882 --> 21:59.970
Get in here.

22:00.014 --> 22:01.929
-Move your feet.
-[thud]

22:01.972 --> 22:03.147
AMANDA: Let's go.

22:04.366 --> 22:05.628
He touched my car.

22:06.934 --> 22:09.545
[voicing silently]

22:09.589 --> 22:11.330
I'm running the age progression
software on the photo

22:11.373 --> 22:13.419
we found at Theresa's.

22:13.462 --> 22:15.116
Your friend?

22:15.159 --> 22:17.336
Mind your business.

22:17.379 --> 22:18.554
Computer's done.

22:18.598 --> 22:20.643
FAITH: Thank goodness.

22:20.687 --> 22:22.384
I still can't place him.

22:22.428 --> 22:24.038
Less facial hair?

22:24.081 --> 22:26.475
[mouse clicking]

22:26.519 --> 22:28.390
That's the mechanic.

22:28.434 --> 22:30.174
Otis Granger.
He's a prepper.

22:30.218 --> 22:32.002
Lives off the grid
at the edge of town.

22:32.046 --> 22:33.264
Then let's be careful.

22:33.308 --> 22:35.223
He could be the next victim
or our killer.

22:35.266 --> 22:37.573
Either way, we've gotta get to
him before any more bodies drop.

22:37.617 --> 22:39.488
Let's go.

22:39.532 --> 22:41.316
[tense music plays]

22:41.360 --> 22:44.450
♪♪

22:44.493 --> 22:45.625
Merrick was
all over the place,

22:45.668 --> 22:47.540
but he definitely
knew something.

22:47.583 --> 22:49.411
What about this guy -- Otis?

22:49.455 --> 22:51.021
Faith said you two bonded.

22:51.065 --> 22:52.501
[chain clanking]

22:52.545 --> 22:53.763
God.

22:53.807 --> 22:55.765
-Otis, hey, it's me.
-[dogs growling, barking]

22:55.809 --> 22:56.810
Remember?

22:56.853 --> 22:59.595
Yeah, you came in
with that Mini.

22:59.639 --> 23:01.162
What are you doing here
with that sheriff?

23:01.205 --> 23:02.772
We're with the GBI, Otis.

23:02.816 --> 23:04.252
You never said that.

23:04.295 --> 23:06.341
You are required
to identify yourselves!

23:06.385 --> 23:07.951
She just did.

23:07.995 --> 23:10.432
-Shut up!
-[barking stops]

23:10.476 --> 23:12.695
OTIS: So that's why you were
poking around my shop.

23:12.739 --> 23:15.132
Probably screwed up
that tire on purpose, too.

23:15.176 --> 23:16.873
♪♪

23:16.917 --> 23:18.309
I am a sovereign citizen!

23:18.353 --> 23:20.442
You have no jurisdiction
on this land.

23:20.486 --> 23:22.618
Otis, hey. It's okay.

23:22.662 --> 23:25.099
I'm just gonna need you
to talk to me

23:25.142 --> 23:27.754
about what happened to that
family in the station wagon.

23:27.797 --> 23:29.146
I ain't got nothing
to do with that.

23:29.190 --> 23:30.539
Go ask Merrick.
He'll tell you.

23:30.583 --> 23:32.280
All right, let's just talk.

23:32.323 --> 23:33.977
Put down the gun, Otis.

23:34.021 --> 23:35.239
[music intensifies]

23:35.283 --> 23:36.415
♪♪

23:36.458 --> 23:39.592
How about I put your gal
down instead?

23:40.854 --> 23:43.683
[somber music plays]

23:43.726 --> 23:45.685
[dogs barking]

23:45.728 --> 23:51.647
♪♪

23:53.344 --> 23:54.824
How's Josie?

23:54.868 --> 23:56.391
First officer-involved shooting.

23:56.435 --> 23:57.914
It's gonna take some time.

23:57.958 --> 23:59.612
A life's a life.

23:59.655 --> 24:00.917
-AMANDA: How's the leg?
-Leg's fine.

24:00.961 --> 24:02.702
I'm pissed off
about the damn suit,

24:02.745 --> 24:04.094
and the fact Otis
gave us nothing.

24:04.138 --> 24:05.356
The guy in the
Chipper Jones jersey

24:05.400 --> 24:07.141
could have moved away
20 years ago,

24:07.184 --> 24:08.229
or be long dead.

24:08.272 --> 24:09.796
Could also be the killer.

24:09.839 --> 24:11.711
Guess I'll go ask Merrick.

24:12.929 --> 24:15.105
Well, we got nothing.
Can't hurt.

24:18.892 --> 24:20.633
[exhales deeply]

24:20.676 --> 24:22.504
FAITH: Hey.

24:22.548 --> 24:26.813
Um, look, I know Amanda
is a lot [chuckles]

24:26.856 --> 24:29.206
but you couldn't have a better
person getting you through this.

24:31.078 --> 24:32.166
Where you headed?

24:32.209 --> 24:33.602
FAITH: To see Merrick.

24:33.646 --> 24:36.126
Sometimes photos can jar
dementia patients' memory.

24:36.170 --> 24:39.478
You know, Merrick was nice to me
when I first started here.

24:39.521 --> 24:40.914
Let me come with you.

24:40.957 --> 24:42.045
I want to see this through.

24:42.089 --> 24:44.047
Let's take your car.

24:44.874 --> 24:46.485
Let's go.

24:48.487 --> 24:50.053
[bicycle bell dinging]

24:50.097 --> 24:52.273
[inquisitive music plays]

24:54.275 --> 24:55.581
Don't trust the
bike rack outside?

24:55.624 --> 24:58.105
Oh, that's not mine.

24:58.148 --> 25:00.716
Don't tell anybody --
I can't ride a bike.

25:00.760 --> 25:02.109
Never learned. Crazy, right?

25:02.152 --> 25:04.546
No, that one's evidence
from a robbery.

25:04.590 --> 25:05.765
What -- What's today?

25:05.808 --> 25:08.028
Tuesday?
I get so --

25:08.071 --> 25:09.943
Tuesday, yeah,
it was scheduled.

25:09.986 --> 25:11.684
I think it's going to
off-site storage next week,

25:11.727 --> 25:14.469
but Otis won't be making
any more pickups, so --

25:14.513 --> 25:17.037
You think Sheriff Miller's
gonna make me do it now?

25:17.080 --> 25:18.734
-I'll have to rent a truck --
-Wait, stop.

25:18.778 --> 25:22.259
You said your off-site evidence
storage is Otis's salvage yard?

25:22.303 --> 25:26.568
♪♪

25:27.830 --> 25:29.179
Hey, give me one of those.

25:29.223 --> 25:30.485
Look, I'm binge eating
as a temporary replacement

25:30.529 --> 25:32.095
for my addiction,
telling myself it'll pass.

25:32.139 --> 25:33.880
-So, no, you cannot have one.
-ANGIE: Okay.

25:33.923 --> 25:35.838
What's going on with you?

25:35.882 --> 25:38.885
Gina Ormewood wants me
to come over for dinner,

25:38.928 --> 25:40.321
-and -- and --
-And?

25:40.364 --> 25:41.931
And I'm crawling
out of my skin, man.

25:41.975 --> 25:43.498
How do I -- In her home?

25:43.542 --> 25:45.848
Look, meeting a partner's spouse
is a time-honored tradition.

25:45.892 --> 25:48.503
She's trusting you
with the father of her kids,

25:48.547 --> 25:50.679
so you go eat
that woman's dry chicken

25:50.723 --> 25:52.202
and if you feel
the pull for a drink,

25:52.246 --> 25:54.596
you come knock on my door
instead, no matter how late.

25:54.640 --> 25:56.206
HELLER: We need those rooms,
Polaski.

25:56.250 --> 25:57.556
You got a confession
coming any time soon?

25:57.599 --> 26:00.167
-Ormewood's real close, Cap.
-[chuckles]

26:00.210 --> 26:03.170
Get it closed, Polaski.

26:04.606 --> 26:05.781
Screw it.

26:05.825 --> 26:06.826
What are you doing?

26:06.869 --> 26:08.131
Finishing it.

26:08.175 --> 26:09.829
I told you,
it takes time, okay?

26:09.872 --> 26:11.352
-It's a solid plan.
-[sighs]

26:11.395 --> 26:13.441
You know what my
least favorite thing is?

26:13.484 --> 26:14.921
Waiting.

26:15.704 --> 26:18.011
Hey.
I know y'all are hungry.

26:18.054 --> 26:20.187
Two candy bars, three of you.

26:20.230 --> 26:22.537
Fight for it, bitches.

26:22.581 --> 26:23.930
[door closes]

26:25.322 --> 26:27.498
-STEVE: Give it to me!
-[rock music plays]

26:27.542 --> 26:30.023
-STEW: I'm hungry!
-STAN: We can split it!

26:30.066 --> 26:33.026
STEVE: You can't split
two things three ways!

26:33.069 --> 26:34.505
STEW: Shut up, Steve!

26:34.549 --> 26:36.725
STAN: We wouldn't be here
if it wasn't for you!

26:37.683 --> 26:39.728
You want to do
the paperwork?

26:39.772 --> 26:41.208
[Steve grunts]

26:41.251 --> 26:42.688
[Ormewood sighs]

26:45.604 --> 26:47.606
JOSIE [whispers]:
Can I have the -- Thanks.

26:48.563 --> 26:51.000
Take a look at this for me,
Dale.

26:51.044 --> 26:53.873
Tell me who you see
in the picture.

26:55.091 --> 26:58.878
It's them, isn't it?

26:58.921 --> 27:01.054
It's them.

27:01.097 --> 27:02.708
Say their names.

27:02.751 --> 27:05.406
[soft, tense music plays]

27:05.449 --> 27:07.147
Allen Cramer.

27:08.757 --> 27:11.281
Otis.

27:11.325 --> 27:12.587
Randy...

27:12.631 --> 27:15.155
♪♪

27:15.198 --> 27:17.766
Who's the other man?

27:17.810 --> 27:19.115
In the jersey.

27:19.159 --> 27:21.683
Chip.

27:21.727 --> 27:22.989
[inhales sharply] Chip.

27:23.032 --> 27:25.078
-Chip.
-Chip's not coming today,

27:25.121 --> 27:26.340
-Sheriff.
-Chip.

27:26.383 --> 27:27.646
Who is Chip?
Do you know Chip?

27:27.689 --> 27:30.474
Chip is Mr. Merrick's
nickname for his son.

27:30.518 --> 27:33.869
Big Chipper Jones fan before
Jones even came to the Braves.

27:33.913 --> 27:35.479
Think he was still playing
high school ball

27:35.523 --> 27:36.872
-in Florida, right?
-MERRICK: Mm-hmm.

27:36.916 --> 27:39.527
Mr. Merrick,
is this your son?

27:39.570 --> 27:41.616
Chip.

27:43.183 --> 27:44.880
Chip.

27:44.924 --> 27:47.013
♪♪

27:47.056 --> 27:49.885
Merrick buried the case
because his son was involved.

27:49.929 --> 27:51.495
I'm headed to pick up
David now.

27:51.539 --> 27:52.888
He's no Otis,
but back in the day,

27:52.932 --> 27:54.411
they were birds of a feather.

27:54.455 --> 27:55.456
I'll be careful.

27:55.499 --> 27:57.937
[cellphone chiming]

27:57.980 --> 27:59.155
It's the lab.

27:59.199 --> 28:00.722
-I'll be right there.
-[cellphone beeps]

28:02.550 --> 28:05.118
Hey, so, uh, how'd you get
Merrick to talk?

28:05.161 --> 28:07.773
Josie came with me
to see Merrick.

28:07.816 --> 28:08.861
WILL: Josie?

28:08.904 --> 28:10.906
She's on administrative leave.

28:10.950 --> 28:13.082
-You know you can't --
-AMANDA: Unbelievable!

28:13.126 --> 28:14.344
Are you kidding me?

28:14.388 --> 28:15.737
I know, I know.

28:15.781 --> 28:17.565
But Josie got him to talk.

28:17.608 --> 28:19.523
Well, Amanda's busy
yelling at the lab,

28:19.567 --> 28:21.134
so consider it a blessing.

28:21.177 --> 28:22.701
[cellphone beeps off]

28:26.226 --> 28:27.793
AMANDA: We sent you the nail!

28:27.836 --> 28:29.664
[stammers] You have it.

28:29.708 --> 28:31.318
I don't want any more excuses!

28:31.361 --> 28:33.146
[cellphone beeps off]

28:33.189 --> 28:35.409
They can't find the nail
from the boat dock?

28:35.452 --> 28:38.064
I told you,
I hate small towns.

28:38.107 --> 28:39.892
[sighs]

28:39.935 --> 28:41.807
Look, let's split up,
find that car.

28:41.850 --> 28:43.547
I'll go this way.

28:48.204 --> 28:50.511
[sighs]

28:50.554 --> 28:55.516
Otis, Mayor Cordett,
Allen Cramer, and David Merrick.

28:55.559 --> 28:57.170
[tense music plays]

28:57.213 --> 28:58.737
Why'd the family park
where they couldn't see

28:58.780 --> 29:00.782
the fireworks display?

29:01.783 --> 29:03.350
Maybe it doesn't matter.

29:03.393 --> 29:04.830
Bugs me, though.

29:04.873 --> 29:08.181
♪♪

29:08.224 --> 29:09.269
And then it happened.

29:09.312 --> 29:11.793
[gunfire]

29:11.837 --> 29:14.796
WILL: They shoot the family,
speed off.

29:14.840 --> 29:17.538
Witness calls it in, but David
already called his father.

29:17.581 --> 29:20.367
The sheriff arrives quickly
to clean up his son's mess.

29:20.410 --> 29:21.411
-[car horn honking]
-WILL: The father

29:21.455 --> 29:22.848
was still alive.

29:22.891 --> 29:24.240
Is that the noise
Merrick was hearing?

29:24.284 --> 29:26.808
You're okay.
I got you. I got you.

29:26.852 --> 29:32.596
♪♪

29:32.640 --> 29:35.295
-[recorder clicks]
-Amanda, over here!

29:40.256 --> 29:41.997
AMANDA: Well this is one way
to cover up a crime --

29:42.041 --> 29:44.391
put one of the killers on the
payroll to hide the evidence.

29:44.434 --> 29:46.393
[inquisitive music plays]

29:46.436 --> 29:51.050
♪♪

29:51.093 --> 29:52.442
Teeth marks?

29:52.486 --> 29:59.536
♪♪

30:12.811 --> 30:14.595
Be right back.

30:14.638 --> 30:15.814
-You good?
-Yep.

30:15.857 --> 30:17.554
Thanks.

30:18.294 --> 30:20.775
[cellphone rings]

30:20.819 --> 30:23.256
[cellphone beeps]

30:23.299 --> 30:26.737
Oh, so you want to be grown
but ask your mother for money?

30:26.781 --> 30:28.565
JEREMY: God, I just called
to say hi, Ma.

30:28.609 --> 30:30.132
Mm-hmm, right.
How much do you need?

30:30.176 --> 30:32.439
And Jeremy,
I can't keep -- Oh.

30:32.482 --> 30:33.832
[gasps]

30:33.875 --> 30:35.137
All right, I'll call you back.

30:35.181 --> 30:36.922
Okay. Ah.

30:38.314 --> 30:40.229
[sighs]

30:40.273 --> 30:41.927
Great. Wonderful.

30:46.453 --> 30:47.889
ELLA JENKINS:
Here's a song that I'm sure

30:47.933 --> 30:49.238
a lot of you will know.

30:49.282 --> 30:51.414
I've been singing it
many, many times

30:51.458 --> 30:52.938
with numerous girls and boys.

30:52.981 --> 30:56.593
♪ Miss Mary Mack, Mack, Mack♪

30:56.637 --> 30:58.508
♪ All dressed in black,
black, black♪

30:58.552 --> 31:00.336
There were teeth marks
on the seatbelt.

31:00.380 --> 31:03.731
♪ With silver buttons,
buttons, buttons♪

31:03.774 --> 31:07.735
The noise Merrick heard
wasn't from a car horn.

31:07.778 --> 31:10.346
WILL: The family didn't care
about the fireworks.

31:10.390 --> 31:11.782
They parked
to feed their baby.

31:11.826 --> 31:14.916
[baby crying]

31:14.960 --> 31:16.309
MERRICK: Oh, my goodness.

31:16.352 --> 31:18.615
You're okay. It's okay.

31:18.659 --> 31:20.704
It's okay. I got you.

31:20.748 --> 31:22.184
Shh.

31:22.228 --> 31:24.404
Don't cry, don't cry.
I got you.

31:24.447 --> 31:28.930
♪ They jumped so high,
high high♪

31:28.974 --> 31:30.932
Girl, I really do hope

31:30.976 --> 31:33.152
you have one of those
bleach pens in here.

31:33.195 --> 31:36.372
♪ And they never came back,
back, back♪

31:36.416 --> 31:40.072
♪ Till the Fourth
of July-ly-ly ♪

31:40.115 --> 31:42.335
[cellphone rings, beeps]

31:42.378 --> 31:43.945
Faith, there was a baby
in the car.

31:43.989 --> 31:46.252
-Will, I just found --
-Listen to me!

31:46.295 --> 31:48.602
I think I know
who the killer is.

31:48.645 --> 31:49.908
♪ Back, back, back♪

31:49.951 --> 31:52.171
I was a baby when it happened.

31:53.302 --> 31:54.869
It's Josie.

31:54.913 --> 31:56.088
[tapping on glass]

31:56.131 --> 31:57.480
JOSIE: Your side arm
and your phone.

31:57.524 --> 31:59.004
Now.

31:59.047 --> 32:00.570
♪ Elephants, elephants,
elephants♪

32:00.614 --> 32:02.007
♪ Jumped the♪

32:02.050 --> 32:04.052
♪ Fence, fence, fence♪

32:04.096 --> 32:05.662
♪ They jumped so♪

32:05.706 --> 32:07.577
♪ High, high, high♪

32:07.621 --> 32:08.883
♪ They touched the♪

32:08.927 --> 32:11.059
-Time to get Chip.
-♪ Sky, sky, sky ♪

32:11.103 --> 32:12.626
♪ And they never came♪

32:12.669 --> 32:14.584
♪ Back, back, back♪

32:14.628 --> 32:15.934
♪ Till the Fourth of July♪

32:17.892 --> 32:19.676
JOSIE: All your buddies
are dead --

32:19.720 --> 32:22.331
Randy Cordett, Cramer, Otis.

32:22.375 --> 32:24.420
[tense music plays]

32:24.464 --> 32:25.769
It's just you now, Chipper.

32:25.813 --> 32:29.208
-Josie, don't.
-I think you know I will.

32:30.078 --> 32:31.558
What...

32:31.601 --> 32:32.951
happened?

32:34.300 --> 32:36.128
We were stupid.

32:36.171 --> 32:37.433
Got drunk,
Allen was driving,

32:37.477 --> 32:38.913
and then we saw
the station wagon.

32:38.957 --> 32:40.697
They were in an area
where nobody was supposed to be.

32:40.741 --> 32:42.395
Were they bothering anybody?

32:42.438 --> 32:44.179
♪♪

32:44.223 --> 32:45.659
DAVID:
We tried talking to them,

32:45.702 --> 32:47.487
but the man
in the station wagon --

32:47.530 --> 32:49.706
You mean my father?

32:51.099 --> 32:53.188
Yeah.

32:53.232 --> 32:55.843
Your father ignored us,

32:55.886 --> 32:57.366
and that pissed off
Allen even more, so he --

32:57.410 --> 33:00.761
No, you!
What did you do, David?

33:03.590 --> 33:04.939
I shot him.

33:04.983 --> 33:11.598
♪♪

33:12.555 --> 33:17.386
Then your daddy went to fix
your mess, but he heard a noise.

33:17.430 --> 33:19.171
He heard me.

33:19.214 --> 33:21.390
My Aunt Louise would have
taken it to her grave,

33:21.434 --> 33:22.913
but I had a heath scare and
needed to know about my family.

33:22.957 --> 33:25.525
So you got into
law enforcement to --

33:25.568 --> 33:27.135
for revenge?

33:27.179 --> 33:29.311
Purpose, Faith.

33:30.399 --> 33:33.315
I wish you hadn't opened
that glove compartment,

33:33.359 --> 33:35.056
but here we are.

33:35.100 --> 33:36.840
So you gonna shoot a GBI agent?

33:36.884 --> 33:39.017
No, sis.
Why would I do that?

33:39.060 --> 33:41.062
I just have to slow you down.

33:41.106 --> 33:44.457
[screams]
Gah! [yelps]

33:45.980 --> 33:49.070
I gave her a hard time
about having a second cellphone.

33:49.114 --> 33:50.463
Thank goodness she did.

33:50.506 --> 33:52.943
We might not have gotten
to her in time.

33:52.987 --> 33:56.077
That's a GBI agent she's got
handcuffed to her hostage.

33:56.121 --> 33:58.384
Keep this and the other end
of the bridge blocked.

33:58.427 --> 34:00.603
No one takes a shot.

34:00.647 --> 34:01.648
Do you understand me?

34:01.691 --> 34:03.911
♪♪

34:03.954 --> 34:05.434
-[men converse indistinctly]
-I'll be damned

34:05.478 --> 34:07.306
if I'm going to lose Evelyn
Mitchell's daughter today.

34:07.349 --> 34:08.916
Let's go get Faith.

34:08.958 --> 34:10.918
♪♪

34:10.960 --> 34:13.007
[breathing heavily]

34:13.051 --> 34:15.922
♪♪

34:15.966 --> 34:17.315
You got your answers.

34:17.359 --> 34:19.318
I heard his confession.
Now let us go.

34:19.360 --> 34:22.451
Faith, you know I didn't
do this for an arrest.

34:22.495 --> 34:23.670
♪♪

34:23.713 --> 34:26.020
[gun cocks]

34:26.063 --> 34:28.283
Faith, talk to me.
You all right?

34:29.067 --> 34:30.893
She's fine! Tell her.

34:30.938 --> 34:32.331
I'm okay.

34:32.373 --> 34:34.027
Suspect's been injured.

34:34.072 --> 34:35.116
GSW to the leg.

34:35.159 --> 34:38.511
Sheriff Miller, I get it.

34:38.554 --> 34:41.166
You want revenge on the people
who hurt your family.

34:41.208 --> 34:44.516
But do you know
who Agent Mitchell is to me?

34:44.560 --> 34:47.172
-She's my family.
-Amanda, don't! Don't!

34:47.824 --> 34:52.568
Josie, you need
to surrender. Now.

34:52.612 --> 34:54.047
[sobbing]
It's already over.

34:54.092 --> 34:56.181
-Your parents, Josie.
-JOSIE: Don't.

34:56.224 --> 34:58.226
Your brother, they loved you.

34:58.270 --> 34:59.923
They're still here with you.

34:59.967 --> 35:01.229
Do you think they would want
their little girl

35:01.273 --> 35:04.014
to be just another dead body
in Lake Lanier?

35:04.058 --> 35:08.062
♪♪

35:08.106 --> 35:09.846
Josie, don't.

35:11.109 --> 35:13.198
Josie, please don't.

35:13.241 --> 35:14.677
Josie! Josie!

35:14.721 --> 35:16.549
FAITH: Please, Josie!

35:16.592 --> 35:20.640
♪♪

35:20.683 --> 35:23.208
[police radio chatter,
sirens wailing]

35:33.827 --> 35:36.090
Please tell me one of those
is a milkshake

35:36.134 --> 35:37.744
that I can crawl into.

35:37.787 --> 35:40.094
Chocolate.

35:42.792 --> 35:44.794
You can have them both
if you want.

35:56.328 --> 35:59.026
They found Josie's body.

35:59.069 --> 36:01.768
[somber music plays]

36:01.811 --> 36:03.770
[inhales deeply]

36:03.813 --> 36:05.772
Oh. [clears throat]

36:06.816 --> 36:08.383
Oh?

36:08.427 --> 36:10.472
W-What's "Oh"?
What are you doing?

36:12.039 --> 36:13.649
Compartmentalizing.

36:13.693 --> 36:16.174
No, I already took
compartmentalizing,

36:16.217 --> 36:17.218
so you're gonna have
to find yourself

36:17.262 --> 36:19.481
another coping mechanism.

36:19.525 --> 36:21.004
It doesn't really work, anyway.

36:21.048 --> 36:22.180
[chuckles lightly]

36:24.269 --> 36:25.357
Your turn.

36:26.706 --> 36:29.187
Tell me something.
One thing.

36:31.624 --> 36:34.322
[sobbing]
It's just so stupid.

36:34.366 --> 36:37.064
I -- I have this
fantasy in my head

36:37.107 --> 36:39.197
where she was swimming
and she swam

36:39.240 --> 36:41.155
and she swam to the other
side of the lake,

36:41.199 --> 36:43.592
and then she got out
and there was a little plane

36:43.636 --> 36:46.378
waiting for her
to take her to Belize or --

36:46.421 --> 36:48.423
or -- or El Salvador.

36:51.034 --> 36:52.253
Yeah.

36:52.297 --> 36:54.864
I like that ending better, too.

36:55.648 --> 36:58.303
The whole thing
is just so sad.

36:58.346 --> 37:01.784
♪♪

37:01.828 --> 37:03.786
And now...

37:05.614 --> 37:08.835
...she's just another ghost.

37:08.878 --> 37:15.929
♪♪

37:31.901 --> 37:33.207
GINA:
Oh, I definitely remember

37:33.251 --> 37:34.382
-Vince's retirement party.
-ANGIE: Yeah. Yeah?

37:34.426 --> 37:35.905
How many fights
broke out that night?

37:35.949 --> 37:37.864
I recall breaking up
at least one.

37:37.907 --> 37:38.908
Vince started it!

37:38.952 --> 37:40.519
GINA: It was his party!

37:40.562 --> 37:42.303
ANGIE [laughing]:
It was his party.

37:42.347 --> 37:45.175
Anyway, these dishes are not
gonna clean themselves,

37:45.219 --> 37:46.829
and no one else
in this house will do it.

37:46.873 --> 37:48.396
-Well, let me help.
-No, no.

37:48.440 --> 37:50.529
You stay put, hang out
with the girls here.

37:50.572 --> 37:52.008
Yeah, just the two,
no more triplets.

37:52.052 --> 37:53.532
ANGIE: Yeah. [chuckles]

37:53.575 --> 37:55.360
[dishes clanking]

38:04.847 --> 38:07.981
[child giggles in distance]

38:08.024 --> 38:10.549
[indistinct conversation
in distance]

38:15.858 --> 38:17.817
[inquisitive,
happy music plays]

38:17.860 --> 38:24.911
♪♪

38:31.221 --> 38:33.833
Mission control,
are we cleared for landing?

38:33.876 --> 38:36.052
Oh, no?

38:36.096 --> 38:37.532
You want to handle this one?

38:37.576 --> 38:41.971
♪♪

38:42.015 --> 38:43.712
Is everything okay
up there?

38:43.756 --> 38:46.802
♪♪

38:46.846 --> 38:48.978
Oh, my gosh.

38:49.022 --> 38:51.938
-Bye, Max, wherever you are.
-Oh, Michael,

38:51.981 --> 38:53.374
can you go upstairs
to check on him?

38:53.418 --> 38:55.463
We cannot afford to have
that tub overflow again.

38:55.507 --> 38:56.986
We could just give him away.

38:57.030 --> 38:58.336
Ha ha.

38:58.379 --> 39:00.599
All right, you two.
Bedtime, upstairs, go.

39:00.642 --> 39:02.078
Mommy, there's monsters.

39:02.122 --> 39:04.342
-No, none of that. Let's go.
-Good night. I love you.

39:04.385 --> 39:06.953
-I want to go with her.
-Let's hit it.

39:06.996 --> 39:08.868
Um, this was really nice.

39:08.911 --> 39:10.217
Thank you, again.

39:10.260 --> 39:12.524
I -- I, uh, I can't remember
the last time I --

39:12.567 --> 39:14.743
Angie, stop.

39:14.787 --> 39:16.397
[sighs]

39:16.441 --> 39:18.921
Look, I invited you here tonight
so I could look you in the eye,

39:18.965 --> 39:21.402
see who you are,

39:21.446 --> 39:22.795
and I get it now.

39:22.838 --> 39:25.275
You're... [voice breaks]

39:26.842 --> 39:30.542
You're that cop who wants
to lock up all the bad guys

39:30.585 --> 39:32.413
and do the right thing

39:32.457 --> 39:34.720
so that no one's
looking at you.

39:34.763 --> 39:36.678
[tense music plays]

39:36.722 --> 39:37.897
I'm -- I'm sorry.

39:37.940 --> 39:39.159
What -- What are you --

39:40.160 --> 39:41.988
Cop wives talk.

39:42.031 --> 39:44.904
♪♪

39:44.947 --> 39:50.997
Kenny Storier's wife
saw you in a parking lot

39:51.040 --> 39:53.260
walking to Michael's car.

39:54.348 --> 39:57.438
I don't know what went on
between you two.

40:00.920 --> 40:03.139
Don't let it happen again.

40:04.967 --> 40:07.187
All right, all you little
monsters better be in bed.

40:07.230 --> 40:14.281
♪♪

40:16.936 --> 40:18.981
[knock at door]

40:20.156 --> 40:22.463
[knocking continues]

40:22.507 --> 40:25.466
[crickets chirping]

40:25.510 --> 40:28.077
-WILL: Hey.
-Hey.

40:28.121 --> 40:30.558
Shut up and listen, okay?

40:30.602 --> 40:32.386
I've been keeping this --

40:32.430 --> 40:33.866
I did something.
[sighs painfully]

40:33.909 --> 40:35.607
Not tonight,
a long time ago,

40:35.650 --> 40:36.956
but I haven't been able
to tell you.

40:36.999 --> 40:38.610
Are you wearing cologne?

40:38.653 --> 40:41.003
No, um... I mean, yes.
It's just --

40:41.047 --> 40:42.614
ANGIE: Sh-Shut up.
It doesn't matter.

40:42.657 --> 40:48.924
♪♪

40:48.968 --> 40:53.146
I slept with Ormewood
a couple years ago.

40:54.321 --> 40:56.410
You -- You two were
seeing each other?

40:57.585 --> 40:59.718
Uh, no. Uh...

40:59.761 --> 41:02.982
You and I were on a break,

41:03.025 --> 41:04.287
and I was high.

41:04.331 --> 41:06.986
I think he was, too.
I don't know.

41:07.029 --> 41:08.335
I was just in his car.

41:08.378 --> 41:11.773
[voice breaking]
It was one time.

41:11.817 --> 41:14.428
Okay, um...

41:17.170 --> 41:19.520
Why are you
telling me this now?

41:19.564 --> 41:22.131
I'm sick of secrets.

41:22.175 --> 41:24.960
That whole time was so bad.

41:25.004 --> 41:26.309
It was so ugly.

41:26.353 --> 41:28.529
And I can't have you
seeing me as ugly.

41:28.573 --> 41:30.575
I don't --
I don't want that.

41:32.141 --> 41:34.100
[exhales sharply]

41:34.143 --> 41:36.319
♪♪

41:36.363 --> 41:38.626
WILL: Ange.

41:40.193 --> 41:42.630
I could never
see you as ugly.

41:42.674 --> 41:49.724
♪♪

41:54.599 --> 41:56.035
I'll, um...

41:56.078 --> 41:58.167
I'll make us
some dinner, okay?

41:58.211 --> 41:59.517
[chuckles]

41:59.560 --> 42:01.562
WILL: Come here.

42:04.565 --> 42:06.698
I just need to make
a phone call.

42:06.741 --> 42:09.222
♪♪

42:11.703 --> 42:18.753
♪♪
